$ Oracle: crash recovery
@ crash recovery

A *crash recovery* happens after either a single-→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance or all instances of a → development/databases/Oracle/Options/real-application-clusters[RAC] environment
crashes when the instance(es) are started up again.

Crash recovery is performed automatically by → development/databases/Oracle, no manual intervention is needed.

Crash recovery only requires (active) → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/online-redo-log-files[online redo log files],
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/archived-redo-log[archived redo log files] are not required.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/recovery
